                    <comment id="12847931" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sun, 21 Mar 2010 15:08:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chris Male mentioned to me that he thinks Uwe has fixed this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12847932" author="thetaphi" created="Sun, 21 Mar 2010 15:18:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is fixed!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But some of the threads use a &quot;own&quot; exception handler calling ex.printStackTrace(), and so those bugs are not detected. But all asserts in foreign threads are fine now!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12847934" author="thetaphi" created="Sun, 21 Mar 2010 15:21:55 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;so unless a failure is caused later from the thread termination, the Asserts are invalid&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is one small problem: The exceptions from external threads are collected on tearDown(). So the assert message is only printed and the test failing in tearDown(). So this does not prevent failures in the main thread before the failures in other thread&apos;s assert statements are detected. But one is sure: The failures are detected and the test is failing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12847939" author="thetaphi" created="Sun, 21 Mar 2010 16:03:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2274&quot; title=&quot;Catch exceptions in Threads created by JUnit tasks&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-2274&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
